+### Observed evidence versus inferred risk
+
+| Finding | Status | Evidence or implication |
+|---|---|---|
+| Wrapping both panes alone is insufficient | Observed | Unequal wrapped heights displaced every later sentinel |
+| Native `scrollbind` still drifts after padding | Observed | `<C-d>` and repeated `<C-e>` diverged on 0.12.2; `:syncbind` did not repair it |
+| Native `scrollbind` oscillates around large virtual filler blocks | Observed and mitigated | The same 60-row filler reproduction failed on Neovim 0.12.2 and 0.13 nightly; renderer-aware synchronization retained exact offsets through and beyond the filler |
+| Window-scoped namespaces isolate visible padding | Observed | Pane-specific filler extmarks rendered only in their scoped windows |
+| `nvim_win_text_height()` honors namespace window filtering | Observed | A three-window scratch test measured each scoped filler only in its owning window; the ordinary window measured none |
+| Custom display-offset synchronization works | Observed | Two- and three-pane sentinels retained matching rows or semantic offsets while scrolling from either side |
+| `WinScrolled` can precede the settled keyboard-scroll view | Observed and mitigated | Immediate synchronization captured a narrow conflict pane one display row early after `<C-d>`; coalescing synchronization onto the next event-loop turn uses the final source view |
+| Neovim 0.13 wraps inline virtual lines | Observed | Inline fixture used `virt_lines_overflow="auto"` on nightly |
+| Move decorations require a settled redraw | Observed | Direct range measurement excludes a leading `virt_lines_above`; the model records move-leading rows and measures after one redraw |
+| Alignment must own a post-decoration transaction | Observed and implemented | Capturing before decoration changes, measuring after one settled redraw, then restoring and synchronizing retained viewport offsets through ordinary and result refreshes |
+| Semantic-token responses need not block alignment | Observed from implementation | The vendored semantic-token path adds highlight extmarks only; it does not add width- or height-affecting text, signs, conceal, or virtual lines |
+| Result signs must exist before wrapped measurement | Observed and implemented | Result refresh now updates conflict signs synchronously before final alignment so `signcolumn=auto` width is settled for the measurement pass |
+| Programmatic result edits need explicit invalidation | Observed in manual harness | A direct `nvim_buf_set_lines()` fixture mutation was followed by `auto_refresh.refresh_result_now()`; normal user edits continue through `TextChanged` debounce |
+| Result edits can produce coarse base mappings | Observed and mitigated | The result composes exact unchanged regions through either input while falling back to its base mapping; incoming/current accepted-block insertion fixtures retained every internal anchor |
+| One global result source is insufficient for mixed edits | Observed and mitigated | Result intervals now select exact unchanged mappings from either input per region and bridge transition gaps; complex accept-both reports `mismatches=0` in both orders |
+| Full Lua suite has one failing spec file | Known upstream issue | `move_keymap_spec.lua` fails `gm aligns moved blocks at same winline()` and the comprehensive all-pairs `gm` case |
+| Large files have measurable cost | Observed | Final cold/warm alignment measured about 8/2 ms at 1k, 72/14 ms at 10k, and 775/75 ms at 100k on Neovim 0.12.2; nightly measured 8/1 ms, 73/15 ms, and 727/78 ms |
+| Layout-toggle shortcuts may miss integration behavior | Inferred risk | Direct buffer rerender bypasses parts of the normal asynchronous update path |
+| Dynamic gutters may invalidate width | Observed and mitigated | Relevant option changes and diagnostics rebuild after final gutter state; unobservable external sign/status providers use explicit invalidation |
+| Arbitrary folds may invalidate height | Observed and mitigated | Fold-aware padding handles one-sided manual folds; compact and fold-option changes rebuild automatically, while manual/external fold commands use explicit invalidation because Neovim has no fold-change event |
+| Dynamic display state may invalidate padding | Partially mitigated | Conceal mode and diagnostics rebuild automatically; arbitrary virtual text/lines and enabled inlay-hint providers use explicit invalidation |
+| View and layout options may fight synchronization | Partially mitigated | `cursorbind` is temporarily disabled and restored, smooth scrolling is mapped, and resize/layout events rebuild; `scrolloff`, `splitkeep`, and external winbar policy remain integration limits |
+| Static display options require invalidation when changed | Implemented | Rendering signatures and `OptionSet` cover line breaking, continuation text, tabs/list rendering, columns, conceal, `ambiwidth`, and `display` |
+
+## Current rendering and alignment model
+
+CodeDiff computes VSCode-style line mappings and always renders line, character, and move decorations. The policy then diverges:
+
+- `wrap=false` retains logical `virt_lines` fillers and opposite-side move fillers, then uses renderer-aware `WinScrolled` synchronization on Neovim 0.12+ with native `scrollbind` as an older-version fallback.
+- Aligned `wrap=true` skips those balancing fillers, builds one n-ary semantic plan, measures settled display heights, adds window-scoped compensation, and uses the same display-facade synchronization primitives.
+
+Relevant files:
+
+- Diff orchestration: `./lua/codediff/ui/view/render.lua`
+- Logical filler calculation and rendering: `./lua/codediff/ui/core.lua`
+- Pure n-ary plan: `./lua/codediff/ui/wrap_alignment_model.lua`
+- Alignment coordinator and invalidation: `./lua/codediff/ui/wrap_alignment.lua`
+- Measurement and compensation: `./lua/codediff/ui/wrap_alignment_renderer.lua`
+- Opaque viewport capture and synchronization: `./lua/codediff/nvim/display/viewport.lua` and `events.lua`
+- Window-scoped padding ownership: `./lua/codediff/nvim/display/layer.lua`
+- Renderer-backed measurement and fold queries: `./lua/codediff/nvim/display/layout.lua`
+- Merge rendering: `./lua/codediff/ui/core.lua`
+- Move annotations and unwrapped-mode fillers: `./lua/codediff/ui/move.lua`
+- Side-by-side window creation: `./lua/codediff/ui/view/side_by_side.lua`
+- Inline rendering: `./lua/codediff/ui/inline.lua`
+- Inline window policy: `./lua/codediff/ui/view/inline_view.lua`
+- Conflict result window: `./lua/codediff/ui/view/conflict_window.lua`
+- Lifecycle re-enforcement: `./lua/codediff/ui/lifecycle/session.lua`
+- Suspend/resume: `./lua/codediff/ui/lifecycle/state.lua`
+- Auto-refresh view restoration: `./lua/codediff/ui/auto_refresh.lua`
+- Resize handling: `./lua/codediff/ui/lifecycle/cleanup.lua`
+
+The retained unwrapped fillers align logical buffer rows, not wrapped screen rows. Enabling wrapping without the measured compensation pass would therefore make all later lines drift when corresponding lines consume unequal display heights.
+
+Example at a 30-column text width:
+
+```text
+original line 3: LLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL
+modified line 3: short
+
+original height: 2 display rows
+modified height: 1 display row
+```
+
+No current filler is generated because both sides contain one logical line. Every subsequent corresponding line is displaced by one screen row.
+
+### Minimal reproduction
+
+1. Create two files containing identical sentinel lines around one changed line.
+2. Make the changed line long on one side and short on the other.
+3. Open the files side by side in CodeDiff.
+4. Enable `wrap` in both panes.
+5. Narrow the panes and scroll below the changed line.
+
+Wrapping both panes is insufficient. Correctness requires equal cumulative display height at every semantic alignment boundary.
+
+The former downstream delayed `wrap=true` workaround in `/home/rich/code/nix-private/out-of-store-config/nvim/plugin/60_git-diff_codediff.lua` has been removed. The local configuration now enables CodeDiff's aligned `diff.wrap` implementation directly.
+
+## Required invariants
+
+For every corresponding alignment boundary:
+
+```text
+display_rows(original prefix)
+  == display_rows(modified prefix)
+  == display_rows(result prefix, when applicable)
+```
+
+Display height includes:
+
+- Wrapped real lines.
+- Logical diff fillers.
+- Wrap-compensation fillers.
+- Move annotations.
+- Compact folds.
+- Inline and end-of-line virtual text.
+- Signs, numbers, fold columns, status columns, and actual pane width.
+- `linebreak`, `breakindent`, `showbreak`, tabs, Unicode width, conceal, and other display-affecting behavior.
+
+Operational invariants:
+
+- Measure after final layout and window options have been applied.
+- Use each pane's actual width; do not assume equal pane widths.
+- Activate wrapped-view synchronization only after padding is current.
+- Keep cursors independent; CodeDiff should not introduce `cursorbind`.
+- Preserve semantic position and `topline`, `topfill`, and `skipcol` where applicable.
+- Rebuild after edit, refresh, resize, layout, fold, file-selection, and resume changes.
+- Never use delayed timers to reapply wrapping.
+- Never perform full-document measurement on `WinScrolled`, `CursorMoved`, or each scroll input.
+
