+## Manual test plan
+
+The primary visual oracle is:
+
+> Every corresponding semantic anchor occupies the same screen row, regardless of which pane initiated scrolling.
+
+Use fixtures with clearly numbered sentinel lines such as `ANCHOR_001`, `ANCHOR_002`, and so on.
+
+For each fixture:
+
+1. Open with wrapping enabled at a wide width.
+2. Narrow panes until corresponding lines wrap differently.
+3. Scroll from each pane using mouse wheel, `<C-e>/<C-y>`, `<C-d>/<C-u>`, Page Up/Down, `zz`, and hunk navigation.
+4. Resize narrower and wider while positioned mid-file.
+5. Edit one side, undo/redo, and trigger refresh.
+6. Confirm sentinels stay aligned, cursors remain independent, and no stale or duplicate fillers appear.
+
+For visible sentinels, compare `screenpos()` rows as an objective check.
