+A repeatable tmux interaction loop is:
+
+```bash
+tmux new-session -d -s codediff-wrap "cd '$PWD' && nvim -u NONE -S overlay/branch/manual-wrap-demo.lua"
+tmux send-keys -t codediff-wrap C-d
+tmux send-keys -t codediff-wrap ':' 'silent WrapReport' Enter
+```
+
+Use a persistent tmux session for interactive fixtures rather than launching Neovim as an ordinary background command. Raw ANSI output or a `Press ENTER` pager from a terminated background Neovim process is not a CodeDiff failure. Prefer `:silent WrapReport` and `:ConflictWrapReport quiet`, then inspect the generated report file.
