+| Neovim 0.12.2 | Smooth `<C-e>/<C-y>` from both panes, unequal-width resize, edit refresh, `linebreak`/`breakindent`/`showbreak`, and bottom-layout conflict scrolling | `skipcol` differed by pane width while absolute offsets and visible anchors stayed equal; compensation-row targets used `topfill`; three-pane offsets remained equal; repeated scrolling kept `rebuild_count=0` |
+| Neovim 0.13 nightly `+41294e4` | Standard render, side → inline at narrow width, wrapped deleted virtual rows, inline → side | Inline `virt_lines_overflow="auto"` wrapped visibly and two-pane equality was restored |
+
+Earlier prototype runs also exercised 0.13 moves, compact folds, center/bottom conflicts, result edits, and explorer interactions. Those modes were rerun after the n-ary refactor on 0.12; a final full 0.13 matrix rerun remains advisable.
+
+Exercise at least:
+
+- `<C-d>`, `<C-u>`, repeated `<C-e>/<C-y>`, Page Up/Down, and scrolling from either pane.
+- `:vertical resize 25` and a later expansion.
+- `t` twice for side-by-side → inline → side-by-side.
+- `gc`, `zR`, `zM`, and individual fold open/close commands.
+- Hunk navigation and `gm` when moves are enabled.
+- Direct edits, undo/redo, and result-buffer edits.
+- Explorer hide/show and file switching.
+- `:tabnew` followed by `:tabprevious` for suspend/resume.
+
+The harness intentionally contains no pass/fail assertions; inspect the report and visible TUI after each interaction.
+
+The sections below are the complete acceptance matrix, not a claim that every item has passed. The support matrix and recorded-runs table are authoritative for completed coverage; unrecorded items remain outstanding.
+
+### Core diff shapes
+
+- Equal-length lines wrapping equally.
+- Long versus short corresponding lines: 2:1, 3:1, and 3:2 rows.
+- Both sides long but wrapping at different words.
+- Long unchanged lines between hunks.
+- Insertions/deletions at beginning, middle, and end.
+- Empty side of an interval.
+- Adjacent and consecutive hunks.
+- Multiline replacements with unequal logical and display height.
+- Empty files and missing final newline.
+
+### Display-width cases
+
+- Tabs beginning at different columns.
+- CJK, emoji, and combining characters.
+- Long unbroken words.
+- Prose using `linebreak`.
+- Indentation using `breakindent` and `showbreak`.
+- `number`, `relativenumber`, `numberwidth`, `signcolumn=auto`, `foldcolumn=auto`, and custom `statuscolumn`.
+- Diagnostics, inlay hints, inline virtual text, virtual lines, `conceallevel`, and `concealcursor`.
+- `linebreak`, `breakindent`, `showbreak`, tabs, `listchars`, and Unicode settings changed after initial alignment.
+- Unequal pane widths and odd terminal widths.
+
+### Mode matrix
+
+- Side-by-side single-file comparison.
+- Explorer switching and refresh.
+- History commit/file switching.
+- Layout and explorer toggles.
+- Move annotations and `gm`.
+- Compact `zo`, `zc`, `za`, `zR`, and `zM` from either pane.
+- Conflict incoming/current/result with all three wrapping differently.
+- Accept ours/theirs/both, manual result edits, undo, resolution, and save.
+- Inline additions, deletions, and replacements with long deleted virtual lines.
+- `wrap=false` inline horizontal behavior.
+
+### Lifecycle and namespace cases
+
+- Same buffer in two CodeDiff sessions at different widths.
+- A third ordinary window showing the same buffer with no CodeDiff fillers.
+- Tabs and layout moves with `splitkeep`, `winfixwidth`, and winbar changes.
+- `scrolloff` and user-enabled `cursorbind` while moving or switching panes.
+- Closing sessions without leaked decorations.
+- Suspend/resume and tab re-entry.
+- Stage/unstage during explorer diff.
+- External file change and auto-refresh.
+- Rapid resize and file switching.
+
+### View and smooth-scroll cases
+
+- Stop partway through a wrapped line.
+- Switch active pane.
+- Resize, edit, and refresh from that position.
+- Confirm correct `topline`, `topfill`, and `skipcol` behavior.
+- Scroll upward and downward across virtual fillers.
+- Check first and last viewport clamping.
+
+### Performance cases
+
+Use 10k- and 100k-line files containing many long lines:
+
+- Initial rendering remains acceptable.
+- Typing and debounced refresh do not freeze the UI.
+- Repeated resize does not accumulate work.
+- File switching does not progressively slow down.
+- Scrolling remains native-speed.
+
+Instrument an alignment rebuild counter during development. Scrolling repeatedly must not increment it; a settled edit or width change should increment it once.
+
+### Regression checks with wrapping disabled
+
+`diff.wrap=false` must preserve:
+
+- Current `nowrap` and synchronized scrolling.
+- Existing logical filler placement.
+- Initial hunk centering and navigation.
+- Move annotations and `gm`.
+- Compact folds.
+- Explorer/history layouts.
+- Conflict editing and result synchronization.
+- Inline horizontal scrolling.
+- Auto-refresh and suspend/resume.
+- User option restoration and extmark cleanup.
+
+The highest-risk acceptance case is the same buffer shown in two differently sized CodeDiff windows plus one ordinary window. It validates the central experimental namespace assumption.
+
+## Product decisions
+
+1. Is Neovim 0.12+ acceptable for aligned multi-pane wrapping, with complete inline wrapping gated to 0.13+?
+2. Is `diff.wrap` a boolean, with `true` guaranteeing aligned wrapping?
+3. CodeDiff temporarily owns `wrap`, `scrollbind`, `smoothscroll`, and `cursorbind` while aligned wrapping is active and restores the captured user values on policy transitions and cleanup.
+4. Which external height-affecting decorations should be supported or suppressed?
+5. Must arbitrary external fold commands remain supported, or can compact folds be CodeDiff-owned?
+6. Should all modes ship together, or should complete two-pane wrapping land before conflict and inline support?
+7. What performance budget is acceptable for initial render, edit refresh, and resize?
+8. Should an explicit `alignment.invalidate(tabpage)` API be exposed for integrations?
+
+## Non-goals
+
+- No timer-based reapplication of `wrap`.
+- No per-scroll full-document recomputation.
+- No hand-written clone of Neovim's wrapping algorithm.
+- No global `diffexpr` mutation.
+- No silent independent-scrolling fallback presented as correct alignment.
+- No unrelated `signcolumn` preference changes.
+- No dedicated mirror buffers unless window-scoped namespace measurement fails.
+
+## Suggested maintainer-facing proposal
+
+### Title
+
+`feat(ui): align wrapped diff panes by measured display rows`
+
+### Description
+
+Add correctly synchronized wrapping using semantic alignment intervals, `nvim_win_text_height()`, and window-scoped filler namespaces. Each pane receives width-specific virtual-row compensation, while lightweight semantic view synchronization replaces native `scrollbind` in all supported multi-pane views. On Neovim 0.13, inline deleted lines use wrapped virtual-line overflow. The implementation avoids timer workarounds, arithmetic wrap estimation, and per-scroll padding recomputation.
